Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller not in court, in custody.  Attorney Richard L. Voss Mr. in court for Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller.  Attorney Francesco Mineo in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a status conference. Defendant's appearance is waived. Court addressed the prompt disposition received on September 8, 2022. Prompt disposition was not signed by the defendant or a witness. Court finds that the prompt disposition request is invalid. If defendant wish to file a prompt disposition, he may do so at a later date. Case is in resolution posture. Parties requested a plea hearing date. Court adjourns case for a plea hearing. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Plea hearing scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Filed: Request for Prompt Disposition Received 9-8-22.

Attorney Richard L. Voss in court, defendant Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller not in court, in custody.  Defendant's appearance waived.  Francesco Mineo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for status conference.  Attorney Richard L. Voss recently appointed and has not received discovery.  Court ordered case adjourned for status conference.  Status conference scheduled for September 21, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Jaymes K. Fenton in court, defendant Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller not in court, in custody.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for Franco Mineo the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Fenton's motion to withdraw due to conflict heard.  Attorney Fenton has explained the conflict to the defendant.  Court finds good cause and allows Attorney Fenton to withdraw as counsel.   Attorney Fenton will notify the SPD office to reappoint counsel.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 25.   All parties are notified that effective July 30, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge David Swanson, Branch 11, in Room 316 of the Safety Building.  Status conference scheduled for August 3, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller in court, defendant in custody with attorney Jaymes K. Fenton appear by video .  Annie Louk appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Detective C.Schachter.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 28.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 14, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
  
*Per Chief Judge Directive 22-04 effective June 13, 2022, this calendar will be assigned to Reserve Judge John Franke, in Room 608 of the Courthouse.

Court ordered no contact with Deshon A. A, Marquita A. H, T-Mobile, Kevin J W
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller in court with attorney Angel L Johnson.  Defendant Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller in custody. Mallory Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jaramiah Javon Rockefeller appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Sanders, Branch 28. Defense challenges counts 1-3. State argues, to amend count 4 due to error with victim initials. Court GRANTS state  verbally amend count 4 victim initials from D.D.A. to M.A.H.. Court advised defendant that due to nature of offense in Count 1-4 a sample of your DNA is required.  If the sheriff's department hasn't already obtained a sample I order them to do so.  There are circumstances that you can request the sample to be expunged from the data base pursuant to statute 165.77(4). Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 18, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
